<item>
            <title>[TIKA-1703] Can&apos;t Specify Tesseract Data Folder Distinct from Tesseract Executable Path</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1703</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a user specifies the path to the Tesseract executable using &lt;tt&gt;TesseractOCRConfig.setTesseractPath&lt;/tt&gt;, then Tika will assume that the Tesseract config folder (usually referred to as the &apos;tessdata&apos; folder) is in the same location. This is usually true in a Windows environment, where everything is installed into a central location.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this is not necessarily the case in a Linux environment. If one were to build Tesseract from source, for example, the config folder will be installed in a different location than the Tesseract executable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One way to fix this would be to add a way to specify the location of the Tesseract config folder separate from the path to the executable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
